ENGR. H. B. NO. 3462 Page 5

1 in t he business of plumbing, or the business of contracting to do
2 plumbing.
3 2. Residential plumbers are limited to one- and two-family
4 dwelling units in a singularly constructed structure with a maximum
5 of two dwelling units and having a minimum of five (5) feet
6 separation of construction to any other dwelling unit or structure
7 regardless and independent of firewalls, such as a single
8 independent residential home or duplex, and does not include
9 occupancies with more than two dwelling units such as apartments,
10 motels, and multifamily townhomes.
11 3. A residential journeyman license entitles the licensee to
12 install plumbing as defined in OAC 158:30-1-2.
